{
  "_about": "Machine-readable Cause & Effect model for the Diamond Light Source B10E 'HeXI' Personnel Safety System (PSS). Source documents: TDI-PSS-B10E-C&E Cause & Effect Matrix v4.0 (14/04/26) and C15862H-HeXI-IOS I/O Schedule. This is a SIL-2 hutch personnel-protection interlock on a HIMax redundant safety PLC. NOTE: 'trip' for a de-energise-to-trip effect means the effect goes to its FAIL-SAFE state (e.g. contactor opens, door unlocks).",

  "voting_legend": {
    "2oo3": "Trips if 2 of the 3 sensors in the group are in the trip state (fault-tolerant, allows 1 failure).",
    "1oo2": "Trips if 1 of the 2 sensors is in the trip state.",
    "1oo4": "Trips if 1 of the 4 sensors is in the trip state (very sensitive, e.g. gas).",
    "1oo7": "Trips if 1 of N (here 8) beam-off buttons is pressed.",
    "1oo1": "Single channel; trips on that one signal."
  },

